light-locker-settings is a simple configuration utility that allows you to 
configure your screensaver and locking settings.

The basic settings controlled by the app currently comprise:
  - Screensaver blank time
  - Enabling/disabling light-locker
  - Controlling locking after screen-blank
  - Enabling/disabling late locking
  - Enabling/disabling lock-on-suspend

Dependencies:
  - Python (2 or 3)
  - python-psutil
  - light-locker

Optional:
  - Settings syncing with xfce4-session and xfce4-power-manager.
    - xfce4-power-manager 1.3.0 or greater is required for this functionality.

Please report comments, suggestions and bugs on
    https://bugs.launchpad.net/light-locker-settings
    
Check for new versions at:
    https://launchpad.net/light-locker-settings